{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# AI/ML Commercialization Decision Engine\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides an interactive walkthrough of the Commercialization Decision Engine. It covers data generation, feature engineering, ML modeling, and the AI insight layer."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Problem Approach & Assumptions\n",
    "\n",
    "Evaluating early-stage AI product concepts for commercial viability is difficult because there is no historical ground truth. We don't know which concepts would have succeeded if built.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Assumptions:**\n",
    "- Concepts with fewer than 3 customer touchpoints across all signals (demo, usage, commercial) are treated as low-confidence by design. Small sample sizes cannot yield high confidence.\n",
    "- High customer feedback scores are necessary but not sufficient; actual usage (e.g. repeat sessions, time spent) and commercial signals (e.g. willingness to pay) carry equal or greater weight.\n",
    "- Delivery complexity must be balanced against expected value. A highly complex product with low expected value is a strong candidate for archiving."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data Design\n",
    "\n",
    "We use realistic, non-uniform distributions to simulate signals:\n",
    "- **Feedback Scores**: Beta-distributed (skewed toward 6-9), reflecting that demos shown to potential customers tend to get favourable but not perfect scores.\n",
    "- **Objection Counts**: Poisson-distributed (most have 0-3, heavy tail).\n",
    "- **Willingness to Pay / Expected Value**: Log-normal distributions (heavy-tailed, reflecting enterprise pricing variance).\n",
    "\n",
    "Data is stored in a relational SQLite database to enforce referential integrity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.data_pipeline.load_to_db import run_pipeline\n",
    "from src.data_pipeline.clean_validate import load_and_clean_all\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rebuild the database from scratch (generates all synthetic data)\n",
    "run_pipeline(reset=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load cleaned data into memory\n",
    "data = load_and_clean_all()\n",
    "concepts_df = data[\"concepts\"]\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(concepts_df)} AI product concepts.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "We engineered 8 core features, mapping raw signals to business meaning. For example, `demand_intensity` is a weighted average of normalized feedback scores, follow-up request rates, and urgency signals."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.features.feature_engineering import build_feature_table\n",
    "\n",
    "features_df = build_feature_table(\n",
    "    concepts_df, \n",
    "    data[\"demo_signals\"], \n",
    "    data[\"usage_signals\"], \n",
    "    data[\"commercial_signals\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "features_df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. ML Models\n",
    "\n",
    "We use a hybrid, two-model approach.\n",
    "\n",
    "### A. KMeans Clustering (Unsupervised)\n",
    "Finds structural similarities in demand. Concepts that cluster tightly with high repeatability across multiple segments are strong candidates for the \"Reusable Asset\" outcome."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.models.clustering import fit_clusters\n",
    "\n",
    "clustered_features = fit_clusters(features_df)\n",
    "clustered_features[['concept_name', 'cluster_id', 'cluster_repeatability_score']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### B. Gradient Boosting Regressor (Supervised-style)\n",
    "We bootstrap a synthetic training label from a documented rule baseline, then train a GBR. \n",
    "\n",
    "**Why GBR instead of a pure rules engine?**\n",
    "A rules engine (linear weighted sum) cannot capture non-linear feature interactions. For example, high engagement is great, but if the decision-maker is never present, the overall readiness should drop non-linearly. GBR learns these interactions, and SHAP explains them clearly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.models.readiness_model import train_readiness_model, predict_readiness_scores, get_feature_importance_df\n",
    "from src.models.confidence import compute_confidence_scores\n",
    "\n",
    "model, x_matrix, x_df = train_readiness_model(clustered_features)\n",
    "readiness_scores = predict_readiness_scores(model, x_matrix, x_df.index.tolist())\n",
    "\n",
    "confidence_scores = compute_confidence_scores(\n",
    "    data[\"demo_signals\"],\n",
    "    data[\"usage_signals\"],\n",
    "    data[\"commercial_signals\"],\n",
    "    clustered_features,\n",
    "    x_df.index.tolist()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Top 3 Global Features:\")\n",
    "print(get_feature_importance_df(model).head(3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Decision Engine & AI Narrative\n",
    "\n",
    "The decision engine maps scores to one of 5 outcomes (Archive, Incubate, Reusable Asset, Customer Pilot, MVP Build) based on a priority matrix.\n",
    "\n",
    "The AI narrative generator uses SHAP values to deterministically generate explainable, business-ready text without relying on external LLM APIs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.insight.decision_engine import run_decision_engine\n",
    "from src.insight.shap_explainer import compute_shap_values, get_top_features_per_concept\n",
    "from src.insight.narrative_generator import generate_all_narratives\n",
    "\n",
    "outcome_df = run_decision_engine(\n",
    "    clustered_features,\n",
    "    readiness_scores,\n",
    "    confidence_scores,\n",
    "    data[\"usage_signals\"],\n",
    "    data[\"demo_signals\"],\n",
    "    data[\"commercial_signals\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "shap_vals = compute_shap_values(model, x_matrix)\n",
    "top_features = get_top_features_per_concept(shap_vals, x_df.index.tolist())\n",
    "\n",
    "narratives = generate_all_narratives(outcome_df, top_features, concepts_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nExample Narrative:\")\n",
    "sample_concept = outcome_df.iloc[0]['concept_id']\n",
    "print(narratives[sample_concept])"
   ]
  }
 ],
